

 ✅ What is Scrum?

Scrum is a framework used in Agile to manage and complete work in small cycles called Sprints.

👉 Agile = Philosophy
👉 Scrum = Practical method to implement Agile

---

 ✅ Important Points in Scrum

---

 1️⃣ Sprint

 Short development cycle (usually 2 weeks)
 At end of sprint → working product is delivered
e Each sprint has fixed time

👉 Small steps, fast delivery

---

 2️⃣ Product Backlog

 List of all features/requirements
 Created and managed by Product Owner
 It keeps changing

Example:

 Login feature
 Payment feature
 Report generation

---

 3️⃣ Sprint Backlog

 Selected items from product backlog
 Work planned for current sprint

👉 Smaller list for 2 weeks

---

 4️⃣ Roles in Scrum

 🟢 Product Owner

 Decides what to build
 Talks with client
 Manages backlog

 🔵 Scrum Master

 Removes obstacles
 Ensures team follows Scrum rules
 Facilitates meetings

 🟡 Development Team(SCRUM Team)

 Developers
 Testers
 Designers(Architects)

---

 5️⃣ Daily Stand-up Meeting

 15-minute daily meeting
 Everyone answers:

  1. What did I do yesterday?
  2. What will I do today?
  3. Any blockers(problems)?

👉 Keeps team aligned

---

 6️⃣ Sprint Planning Meeting

 Done at start of sprint
 Team selects work from backlog
 Work is estimated

---

 7️⃣ Sprint Review Meeting

 Done at end of sprint
 Team shows working product to client
 Feedback collected

---

 8️⃣ Sprint Retrospective Meeting

 Team meeting to improve process
 Discuss:

   What went well?
   What can improve?

---


 1️⃣ User Story

A small requirement written from user perspective.

Format usually:

> As a user, I want feature, so that benefit.
As a user, i want login page, so that
i can loginw ith a valid username and valid password

Example:

> As a user, I want to login so that I can access my account.

---

 2️⃣ Story Points

Used to estimate effort of a task.

Instead of hours, Scrum uses numbers like:

Planning Poker
1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13

Example:

 Simple login page → 3 points
 Payment integration → 8 points

---

 3️⃣ Velocity

Amount of work completed in one sprint.

Example:

Sprint 1 → 20 story points
Sprint 2 → 25 story points

Average velocity = ~22 points

Helps plan future sprints.

---

 4️⃣ Epic

A large feature that contains multiple user stories.

Example:

Epic = Payment System

User Stories inside it:

 Add credit card
 Pay using card
 View payment history

---

 5️⃣ Task

Small technical work required to complete a story.

Example:

User Story: Login Feature

Tasks:

 Create login UI
 Write API
 Write test cases

---

 6️⃣ Burndown Chart

A graph showing remaining work vs time.

Goal:
Work should go down to zero before sprint ends.

Used to track sprint progress.

---

6️⃣ Burnup Chart ==> oppopsite of Burndown chart

 
